<div id="Idea_2671"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/2671-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_2671">An educated populace is necessary for good government&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/0-4049">jhorne18</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">10 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">As was observed by both Plato and Aristotle 2500 years ago, an educated population is necessary for democratic processes to work.  Simply establishing machinery for access to decision makers is not enough.  To achieve the goal of an educated population, one must reconstitute the school system. This means establishing a mandatory curriculum that includes philosophy and critical thinking at all levels.   Getting people to participate in decision making always has been a serious problem, as people are so concerned with the every day minutiae of their lives.  Too, one must ask at what level and to what degree should they participate.  Government is so large and often overwhelming.  The mechanics outlined on this website help, but, again, education must come first.</div>
